## Proposed Changes

### Lib — AI Service Layer

#### [NEW] [openai.ts](file:///Users/abdulmajeed/Downloads/DiskDoctor/src/lib/openai.ts)

OpenAI client helper that initializes from the stored API key. Functions:

- `getOpenAIClient(apiKey: string)` — creates an OpenAI client instance
- `generateBlogContent(params)` — calls GPT-4o with a detailed system prompt to generate: title, slug, content (HTML), excerpt, meta description, focus keyword, tags, category. The system prompt will include DiskDoctor's brand context, SEO best practices from your [BLOG_SEO_GUIDE.md](file:///Users/abdulmajeed/Downloads/DiskDoctor/docs/BLOG_SEO_GUIDE.md), and the company's service areas.
- `generateFeaturedImage(title, description)` — calls DALL-E 3 to create a 1792×1024 image, then uploads to Cloudinary and returns the URL.
- `analyzeBlogsAndSuggestTopic(existingTitles[], existingContent[])` — for MagicAI mode: sends existing blog summaries to GPT-4o and asks it to identify content gaps and suggest a unique, trending topic.

#### [NEW] [types.ts changes](file:///Users/abdulmajeed/Downloads/DiskDoctor/src/lib/types.ts)

Add new interfaces:

```typescript
export interface AISettings {
    type: 'ai_config';
    provider: 'openai';
    apiKey: string;
    model: string;            // 'gpt-4o', 'gpt-4o-mini'
    imageModel: string;       
    updatedAt: string;
}

export interface AIGenerateRequest {
    mode: 'guided' | 'magic';
    topic?: string;           // guided mode: user's topic
    notes?: string;           // guided mode: additional instructions
    targetWordCount?: number; // default 1200
}

export interface AIGenerateResponse {
    title: string;
    slug: string;
    content: string;          // HTML
    excerpt: string;
    metaDescription: string;
    focusKeyword: string;
    category: string;
    tags: string[];
    featuredImage: string;    // Cloudinary URL
}
```

