## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

Since there are no existing tests in this project, verification will be manual:

1. **Settings flow**: Go to `/admin/dashboard` → click settings gear → enter OpenAI API key → click "Test Connection" (verify it shows ✅) → click "Save" → refresh page (verify key persists from MongoDB)

2. **Guided generation**: Click MagicAI button → select "Guided" tab → enter topic "Signs your SSD is dying" → click Generate → wait for progress steps → verify it redirects to editor with all fields pre-filled (title, content, SEO fields, featured image) → verify the content is relevant, well-structured HTML, and ~1200 words

3. **MagicAI generation**: Click MagicAI button → "MagicAI" tab → click "Auto Generate" → wait → verify the chosen topic is unique (different from existing blog titles) → verify editor pre-fills correctly

4. **Edge cases**: Try generating without API key configured (should show error), try with an invalid API key (should show clear error on test connection), try generating with no existing blogs (MagicAI should still work)

5. **Published blog check**: After AI generates a blog → review in editor → click Publish → verify the blog appears on `/blog` with correct content, images, and SEO metadata

> [!NOTE]
> Since these tests require a real OpenAI API key, they need to be run manually by you. I'll verify the code compiles and the UI renders correctly using the browser tool.
